returns._0: The value of the slot as bytes32

params.slots: List of slots to SLOAD from.

returns.feeDelta: The balance delta of the fees generated in the liquidity range.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

swap((address,address,address,address,ui.details: Swapping on low liquidity pools may cause unexpected swap amounts when liquidity available is less than amountSpecified. Additionally note that if interacting with hooks that have the BEFORE_SWAP_RETURNS_DELTA_FLAG or AFTER_SWAP_RETURNS_DELTA_FLAG the hook may alter the swap input/output. Integrators should perform checks on the returned swapDelta.

params.hookData: Any data to pass to the callback

returns.delta: The balance delta of the address swapping

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateDynamicLPFee((address,address,addr.details: Some of the use case could be:   1) when hook#beforeSwap() is called and hook call this function to update the lp fee   2) For BinPool only, when hook#beforeMint() is called and hook call this function to update the lp fee   3) other use case where the hook might want to on an ad-hoc basis increase/reduce lp fee

donate((address,address,address,address,.notice: Donate the given currency amounts to the pool with the given pool key

extsload(bytes32[]).notice: Called by external contracts to access sparse pool state

getPoolBitmapInfo(bytes32,int16).notice: Get the tick bitmap info about a specific range (a word range) in the pool

getPoolTickInfo(bytes32,int24).notice: Get the tick info about a specific tick in the pool

getPosition(bytes32,address,int24,int24,.notice: Get the position struct for a specified pool and position

getSlot0(bytes32).notice: Get the current value in slot0 of the given pool

grantPausableRole(address).notice: Grant the pausable role to an account, called by the owner

initialize((address,address,address,addr.notice: Initialize the state for a given pool ID

modifyLiquidity((address,address,address.notice: Modify the position for the given pool

pause().notice: Pause the contract, called by the owner or an account with the pausable role

revokePausableRole(address).notice: Revoke the pausable role to an account, called by the owner

setProtocolFee((address,address,address,.notice: Sets the protocol's swap fee for the given pool

setProtocolFeeController(address).notice: Update the protocol fee controller, called by the owner
